code: import os import pandas as pd import numpy as np import torch import torch.nn as nn from torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split # Model architecture fix class LSTMRegressor(nn.Module): def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size, num_layers): super().__init__() self.lstm = nn.LSTM(input_size, hidden_size, num_layers, batch_first=True) self.linear = nn.Linear(hidden_size, 1) def forward(self, x): out, _ = self.lstm(x) # Extract sequence outputs return self.linear(out) # Apply linear layer to each timestep # Data preprocessing with improved normalization def normalize_group(df_group): df_group = df_group.copy() df_group["u_in_cumsum"] = df_group["u_in"].cumsum() eps = 1e-7 # Normalize time-varying features per breath for col in ["u_in", "u_in_cumsum", "time_step"]: min_val = df_group[col].min() max_val = df_group[col].max() df_group[col] = (df_group[col] - min_val) / (max_val - min_val + eps) # Normalize static features using global stats df_group["R"] = (df_group["R"] - 5) / (50 - 5) df_group["C"] = (df_group["C"] - 10) / (50 - 10) return df_group # Load and preprocess data train_df = ( pd.read_csv("input/train.csv") .groupby("breath_id") .apply(normalize_group) .reset_index(drop=True) ) test_df = ( pd.read_csv("input/test.csv") .groupby("breath_id") .apply(normalize_group) .reset_index(drop=True) ) # Dataset class remains same class VentilatorDataset(Dataset): def __init__(self, df, is_train=True): self.breath_groups = [g for _, g in df.groupby("breath_id")] self.is_train = is_train def __len__(self): return len(self.breath_groups) def __getitem__(self, idx): group = self.breath_groups[idx] features = torch.FloatTensor( group[["u_in", "u_out", "time_step", "u_in_cumsum", "R", "C"]].values ) if self.is_train: return features, torch.FloatTensor(group["pressure"].values) return features # Initialize model and training params device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu") model = LSTMRegressor(input_size=6, hidden_size=256, num_layers=3).to(device) optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001) loss_fn = nn.L1Loss() # Create train/val split breath_ids = train_df["breath_id"].unique() train_breath_ids, val_breath_ids = train_test_split( breath_ids, test_size=0.2, random_state=42 ) train = train_df[train_df["breath_id"].isin(train_breath_ids)] val = train_df[train_df["breath_id"].isin(val_breath_ids)] train_loader = DataLoader( VentilatorDataset(train), batch_size=128, shuffle=True, num_workers=4, pin_memory=True, ) val_loader = DataLoader( VentilatorDataset(val), batch_size=256, shuffle=False, num_workers=4, pin_memory=True, ) # Training loop with dimension fix best_val = float("inf") for epoch in range(15): model.train() train_loss = 0 for features, targets in train_loader: features, targets = features.to(device), targets.to(device) optimizer.zero_grad() outputs = model(features) loss = loss_fn(outputs.squeeze(-1), targets) # Fix dimension squeeze loss.backward() optimizer.step() train_loss += loss.item() * len(features) # Validation model.eval() val_loss = 0 with torch.no_grad(): for features, targets in val_loader: features, targets = features.to(device), targets.to(device) outputs = model(features) val_loss += loss_fn(outputs.squeeze(-1), targets).item() * len(features) avg_val = val_loss / len(val) print(f"Epoch {epoch+1}: Val MAE {avg_val:.4f}") if avg_val < best_val: best_val = avg_val torch.save(model.state_dict(), "best_model.pth") # Generate submission model.load_state_dict(torch.load("best_model.pth")) model.eval() test_ds = VentilatorDataset(test_df, is_train=False) test_loader = DataLoader(test_ds, batch_size=256, shuffle=False) preds = [] with torch.no_grad(): for features in test_loader: features = features.to(device) preds.append(model(features).cpu().numpy().squeeze().flatten()) submission = pd.DataFrame({"id": test_df["id"], "pressure": np.concatenate(preds)}) submission.to_csv("submission/submission.csv", index=False) print(f"Best Validation MAE: {best_val:.4f}, Submission saved")
